cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with secure and distributed aggregation, which involves cryptography, distributed systems, and data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also uses Kademlia, a distributed hash table, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves data structures and algorithms, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper mentions complex voting protocols, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
